                <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/> <lb n="1"/>domo Mursa <expan><abbr>vix</abbr><ex>it</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>an</abbr><ex>nos</ex></expan> XXXVI <expan><abbr>stip</abbr><ex>endiorum</ex></expan> XVIII Aurelia <lb n="3"/>Priscilla co&amp;lt;n=I&amp;gt;iux <expan><abbr>eiu</abbr><ex>s</ex></expan> <lb n="4"/>Prisca et Probilla filias <note>sic</note> <lb n="5"/>et <expan><ex>h</ex><abbr>eredes</abbr></expan> posuerunt qui <lb n="6"/>defunctus est Per&amp;lt;i=E&amp;gt;<expan><abbr>nt</abbr><ex>h</ex></expan>&amp;lt;i=O&amp;gt; <lb n="7"/>et ossua <note>sic</note> ei<surplus>i</surplus>us in <expan><ex>h</ex><abbr>unc</abbr></expan> <note>sic</note> <expan><abbr>loc</abbr><ex>um</ex></expan> <note>sic</note> <lb n="8"/>sunt 
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Inschriftträger: (TitAq) Ossuarium. Heute aufliegender Deckel nicht zugehörig. Tod des Soldaten im Winter 193/194 in Perinth. Die Beisetzung der Knochen erfolgte später, vermutlich nach Rückkehr der legio II adiutrix 196 n. Chr. (s. TitAq).</p>
            </div>
